<p>The closest I got to is:  </p>  <pre><code>@Override public void onConfigurationChanged(Configuration newConfig) {     super.onConfigurationChanged(newConfig);     if (newConfig.orientation == Configuration.ORIENTATION_PORTRAIT)     {         InputMethodManager inputMethodManager = (InputMethodManager) getSystemService(Context.INPUT_METHOD_SERVICE);         inputMethodManager.hideSoftInputFromWindow(input.getWindowToken(), 0);     }     //Some other code } </code></pre>  <p>But that doesn't work. In this case, even if no input has focus, the keyboard will be pulled up, once the orientation is changed to portrait.</p>